In line with Federal government policy that there should not be physical railway Level Crossing at road intersections linking railway lines, China Civil Engineering Construction Corporation (CCECC) has gotten approval for the construction of nine underpasses and bypasses within Lagos metropolis along the corridor of ongoing construction of Lagos to Ibadan Standard gauge railway line. Managing Director, Nigerian Railway Corporation (NRC) Engr.First Okhiria who disclosed this on Friday in Lagos while fielding questions from Journalists after inspection of the Ebute-Metta to Apapa axis of the ongoing construction of Lagos to Ibadan standard gauge railway line said the underpasses and overpasses would be located at Yaba, Jibowu, Mushin, Shogunle, Ikeja, Oshodi, Agege, Iju, Agbado amongst others He explained further that construction of bypasses and underpasses at rail, road inter-sections was not in the original contract agreement hence the need to seek for government approval. According to Okhiria soon after approval by government the bridges had to be designed depending on topography and location of each level crossing. The managing director also said that more space would have to be acquired at the locations designated for construction of underpasses and bypasses before commencement of work. He attributed delay in the construction of the railway stations to the fact that vessels conveying some of the building materials are awaiting to berth. 